      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I ignore the comment and I read the code, I see the following:\n\n_\"If the current local ref hasn\u0027t changed from the initial one, *OR* the current one is equal to the destination ref, *OR* the local ref has been removed, then accept the fetch\"_\n\nThe above condition seems unrelated with the comment and also unrelated to the purpose of this change, for the following reasons:\n\n1. If the current local ref hasn\u0027t changed from the initial one, I still need to check if the new ref would be a fast-forward or not. I cannot simply accept it as-is.\n\n2. If the current local ref is the destination ref, then the update type won\u0027t be a `UPDATE_NONFASTFORWARD` anyway, so the code at L275 won\u0027t be triggered.\n\n3. If the current local ref has disappeared, I believe it should be rejected as it isn\u0027t a fast-forward.\n\nI\u0027d suggest just removing this block.\n\n\n\n```suggestion\n\n\t\t\t\tObjectId currentId \u003d currentObjectId(cmd.getRefName());\n```",
